pullRequest.bodyText:
Added 'Battery Low' profile -> Changed to 'Hysteresis' Profile

This profile is useful to implement a user-defined threshold for battery low warning. Sometimes a vendors create a battery low  warning themselves based on a fixed value - which may not be useful from users pov - beside delivering a battery level for devices. In other cases the bindings developers add a estimation in their code to deliver battery low warning (like e.g. Hue or TRADFRI).
How does it work:
The profile configuration needs a mandatory lower bound (lower) config parameter and an optional upper bound (upper) config parameter - will be set to lower bound, if missing. The resulting Switch will change to ON if the value drops below the lower bound. It will change to OFF if the value exceeds upper bound.
Configuration:
Switch hysteresisResult0 {
    channel="..." [profile="system:hysteresis", lower=10, inverted=true]
}
Switch hysteresisResult1 {
    channel="..." [profile="system:hysteresis", lower=10, upper=40]
}
Switch hysteresisResult2 {
    channel="..." [profile="system:hysteresis", lower="10 cm", upper="2 m"]
}
Signed-off-by: Christoph Weitkamp github@christophweitkamp.de
